item.title: COVID-19 on Diferent Aspects from Toronto Cases
item.description: Abstract In this paper I will explore the data of COVID-19 cases from Toronto, and analyzing it in different aspects such as gender groups, age groups, fatal and resolved cases. Also, I will develop a model to pursue deeper influences from the variables and to know the level of influences by each variable. resou <- list_package_resources("https://open.toronto.ca/dataset/covid-19-cases-in-toronto/") covdat <- get_resource(resou) str(covdat) ## tibble [17,872 x 18] (S3: tbl_df/tbl/data.frame) ## $ _id : int [1:17872] 143647 143648 143649 143650 143651 143652 143653 143654 143655 143656 .
